OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FScrap tax on sunscreen, say
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcancer charities           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Value added tax - better known as VAT -
OL,6, should be scrapped on sunscreen to make
OL,7, it more affordable, say several UK     
OL,8, cancer charities.                      
OL,10,FSunscreen is classified as a "cosmetic"
OL,11,Fproduct and carries a 20% tax, adding  
OL,12,Faround #1.50 to the cost of a bottle.  
OL,14,FCharities want high-factor protective  
OL,15,Fcreams to be VAT exempt, citing the    
OL,16,Fcost-of-living crisis which has seen   
OL,17,Fmany struggling to buy essential items.
OL,19,FMost skin cancers are caused by sun    
OL,20,Fdamage.                                
